text: Robert Peters (born 15 November 1970) is an Antiguan former cyclist. He competed in two events at the 1992 Summer Olympics. ==References== Category:1970 births Category:Living people Category:Antigua and Barbuda male cyclists Category:Olympic cyclists of Antigua and Barbuda Category:Cyclists at the 1992 Summer Olympics Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
